e/tigerair-to-operate-under-scoot-brand-from-july-8948362 |website=Channel NewsAsia |date=15 June 2017 |accessdate=7 September 2019}}</ref>\n* 27 July \u2013 [[Amazon (company)|Amazon]] launches its services in Singapore, along with its new HQ.<ref>{{cite web |title=Amazon officially launches in Singapore |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/amazon-officially-launches-singapore |publisher=Todayonline |date=27 July 2017 |accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref>\n* 28 July \u2013 [[NTUC FairPrice|FairPrice]] launches its first unstaffed, cashless Cheers store in [[Nanyang Polytechnic]]. A QR code will be required for access to the store.<ref>{{cite web |title=Launch of The Cheers Unmanned Store at Nanyang Polytechnic |url=https://www.mti.gov.sg/Newsroom/Speeches/2017/07/Speech-by-Minister-Iswaran-at-the-Launch-of-the-Cheers-Unmanned-Store |publisher=MTI |date=28 July 2017 |accessdate=6 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Cheers launches first unmanned, cashless store in Singapore |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/cheers-launches-first-unmanned-cashless-store-in-singapore-9072076 |publisher=CNA |date=28 July 2017 |accessdate=6 August 2019}}</ref>\n* 29 July \u2013 [[East Coast Park]] will be refreshed in upgrading plans announced.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/east-coast-park-to-be-upgraded-with-more-open-spaces-and-amenities|title=East Coast Park to be upgraded with more open spaces and amenities|date=29 July 2017|work=The Straits Times|access-date=5 July 2019|language=en-SG}}</ref>\n\n===August===\n* 1 August \u2013 A ban on [[point of sale display]] of [[tobacco products]] takes effect to reduce the appeal of cigarettes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/ban-on-point-of-sale-display-of-tobacco-products-from-aug-1-2017-retailers-will|title=Ban on point-of-sale display of tobacco products from Aug 1, 2017; retailers will have 1-year grace period|date=28 July 2016|work=The Straits Times|a