 its 27th SEA Games gold medal in men's water polo. This is the country's longest winning streak in the sport.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sg.news.yahoo.com/sea-games-mens-water-polo-slideshow-wp-053606658.html|title=SEA Games: Men's water polo team earn 27th gold medal in dominant fashion|last=Chin|first=Nigel|date=20 August 2017|work=Yahoo News Singapore|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170824140137/https://sg.news.yahoo.com/sea-games-mens-water-polo-slideshow-wp-053606658.html|archive-date=24 August 2017|url-status=live|language=en-SG|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n**Several new plans are unveiled. There will be 40,000 more pre-school places by 2022, with new Early Years Centres (EYCs) for children up to 4 years old, leading to MOE Kindergartens catering to children aged 5 and 6. The [[Ministry of Education (Singapore)|Ministry of Education]] will set up 50 kindergartens by 2023 compared to 15 now. In addition, a National Institute of Early Childhood Development will be set up under the [[National Institute of Education]] to raise pre-school teachers' standards.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Goy |first1=Priscilla |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/national-day-rally-2017-more-childcare-places-and-moe-kindergartens-new-institute-for-pre |title=National Day Rally 2017: More childcare places and MOE kindergartens; new institute for pre-school teachers |website=The Straits Times |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=20 August 2017}}</ref> In addition, bilingual education will be emphasised at a young age.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Yong |first1=Charissa |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/national-day-rally-a-boost-in-bilingualism-for-pre-school-pupils |title=National Day Rally 2017: A boost in bilingualism for pre-school pupils |website=The Straits Times |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=20 August 2017}}</ref> Other plans include smart lamp posts as part of the Smart Nation Sensor Platform (SNSP) for surveillance and data collection,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tham |first1=Irene |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/national-day-rally-2017-smart-lamp-posts-to-become-key-nodes-for-surveillance-and-data |title=National Day Rally 2017: 'Smart' lamp posts to become key nodes for surveillance and data collection |website=The Straits Times |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=20 August 2017}}</ref> Parking.sg app to reduce reliance on coupons,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tham |first1=Irene |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/national-day-rally-2017-new-mobile-app-to-put-an-end-to-parking-coupons-from-october |title=National Day Rally 2017: Parking goes coupon-free from October with mobile app |website=The Straits Times |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=20 August 2017}}</ref> and several moves to encourage cashless transactions.<ref>{{cite web |title=PM Lee Hsien Loong's National Day Rally speech: All you need to know in 3 minutes |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/pm-lees-national-day-rally-speech-all-you-need-to-know-in-3-minutes |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=13 June 2019 |date=20 August 2017}}</ref> Several moves to curb [[diabetes]] are announced too,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lai |first1=Linette |title=National Day Rally 2017: Soft drink companies pledge to reduce sugar in drinks |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/national-day-rally-2017-soft-drink-companies-pledge-to-reduce-sugar-in-drinks |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=7 November 2019 |date=20 August 2017}}</ref> with seven drink companies pledging to lower sugar content in drinks to 12 percent two days later.<ref>{{cite web |title=Seven drink companies pledge to reduce sugar in beverages to 12% or less by 2020 |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/seven-drink-companies-pledge-to-reduce-sugar-in-beverages-to-12-or-less-by-2020 |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=13 June 2019 |date=22 August 2017}}</ref>\n* 21 August \u2013 \n**10 US marines perished after destroyer USS John S. McCain collided with an oil tanker Alnic MC east of Singapore at 5:24am.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/08/20/asia/us-navy-destroyer-collision-singapore/index.html|title=Navy continues search for sailors, wants answers|last=Lendon|first=Brad|date=21 August 2017|work=CNN|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170824074149/http://www.cnn.com/2017/08/20/asia/us-navy-destroyer-collision-singapore/index.html|archive-date=24 August 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> All the bodies are found on 28 August.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tan |first1=Audrey |title=Remains of all 10 sailors missing from USS John S. McCain collision found: US 7th Fleet |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/remains-of-all-10-sailors-missing-from-uss-john-s-mccain-collision-found-us-7th-fleet |website=The Straits Times |date=28 August 2017 |accessdate=19 September 2019}}</ref>\n**Touche, a biometric payment method part of the POSB Smart Buddy programme, will be an option for students to pay for items in school from 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/biometric-payment-system-to-be-an-option-in-schools-in-2018-9142490 |title=Biometric payment system to be an option in schools in 2018 |website=Channel NewsAsia |date=21 August 2017 |access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref>\n* 22 August \u2013 [[Alipay]] will be launched in Singapore.<ref>{{cite web |title=AliPay to launch local wallet for Singapore |url=https://www.todayonline.com/business/impact/alipay-launch-local-wallet-singapore-soon |website=Todayonline |date=22 August 2017 |accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref> Since then, [[Grab (company)|Grab]], [[NETS (company)|NETS]], [[Razer Inc.|Razer]], among other companies have announced plans to set up cashless systems.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ride-hailing app Grab launches e-payment and fund transfer system |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/tech/ride-hailing-app-grab-launches-e-payment-and-fund-transfer-system |website=The Straits Times |date=30 August 2017 |accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"NETSpay\">{{cit