est. This comes after Mediacorp announced that it will stop publishing the [[Today\u00a0(Singapore newspaper)|Today]] paper and go fully digital. In addition, Mediacorp will stop publishing any soft copy or digital format of Today that is similar to a hardcopy newspaper for five years.<ref>{{cite web |title=SPH to divest stakes in Mediacorp entities |url=https://sph.com.sg/media_releases/3283 |website=SPH |date=25 August 2017 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Mediacorp buys SPH\u2019s minority shareholdings of its entertainment television and newspaper businesses |url=https://www.mediacorp.sg/en/corporate/mediacorp-in-the-news/media-releases/mediacorp-buys-sph-s-minority-shareholdings-of-its-entertainment-9157914 |website=Mediacorp |date=25 August 2017 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=TODAY moves to a fully digital future |url=https://www.mediacorp.sg/en/mediacorp-in-the-news/media-releases/today-moves-to-a-fully-digital-future-9157934 |website=Mediacorp |date=25 August 2017 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Yahya |first1=Yasmine |title=SPH to divest stakes in Mediacorp TV and Press while Today newspaper will cease print edition and go fully digital |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/companies-markets/sph-to-divest-stakes-in-mediacorp-tv-and-press-while-today-newspaper-will |website=The Straits Times |date=25 August 2017 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Today\">{{cite web |last1=Mokhtar |first1=Faris |title=TODAY goes fully digital from Oct, to end print edition after 17-year run |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/today-go-full-digital-oct-end-print-edition-after-17-year-run |website=Today |date=25 August 2017 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=TODAY newspaper to cease print edition, go fully digital |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/today-newspaper-to-cease-print-edition-go-fully-digital-9157872 |website=Channel NewsAsia |d