 MRT station to have crossover track to minimise train service disruptions |website=The Straits Times |access-date=1 November 2019 |date=11 September 2017}}</ref>\n**[[2017 Singaporean presidential election|2017 Presidential Election]]: former [[Speaker of Parliament (Singapore)|Speaker]] [[Halimah Yacob]] is announced by the Presidential Elections Commission as the only candidate issued with both the certificate of eligibility and community certificate.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/halimah-yacob-only-one-to-get-eligibility-certificate-set-to-be-singapores-next-president|title=Halimah Yacob only one to get eligibility certificate, set to be Singapore's next President|last=Yong|first=Charissa|date=11 September 2017|work=The Straits Times|access-date=14 September 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n* 13 September \u2013 \n** Two ships collide near Singapore waters, causing two casualties and seven injured, with another three missing.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/two-ships-collide-in-singapore-waters-five-crew-members-missing|title=Two ships collide in Singapore waters; 7 injured, 2 dead, 3 missing|last=Lai|first=Linette|date=14 September 2017|work=The Straits Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190125020540/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/two-ships-collide-in-singapore-waters-five-crew-members-missing|archive-date=25 January 2019|url-status=live|last2=Seow|first2=Bei Yi|language=en|last3=Au-Yong|first3=Rachel|access-date=6 April 2019|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n** Nomination day for the [[2017 Singaporean presidential election|2017 Presidential Election]]: former [[Speaker of Parliament (Singapore)|Speaker]] Halimah Yacob won the election via an [[walkover|uncontested walkover]] since she was the only candidate eligible to contest in the election (the third such walkover after [[1999 Singaporean presidential election|1999]] and [[2005 Singaporean presidential election|2005]]),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businesstimes.com.sg/government-economy/presidential-election-2017/halimah-yacob-declared-president-elect-after-walkover|title=Halimah Yacob declared president-elect after walkover victory|first=Lee|last=U-Wen|publisher=Channel NewsAsia|accessdate=13 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170913080026/http://www.businesstimes.com.sg/government-economy/presidential-election-2017/halimah-yacob-declared-president-elect-after-walkover|archive-date=13 September 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> and was inaugurated as the eighth, and first female [[President of Singapore]] a day later.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/president-halimah-yacobs-full-speech-at-her-swearing-in-ceremony-at-the-istana|title=President Halimah Yacob's full speech at her swearing-in ceremony at the Istana|date=14 September 2017|work=The Straits Times|access-date=26 November 2019|language=en}}</ref>\n* 15 September \u2013 \n**Gavin Chan dies due to injuries relating [[Bionix AFV]] in [[Queensland]], Australia;<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/nsf-death-armoured-vehicle-lands-on-side-while-getting-out-of-9223014|title=NSF death: Armoured vehicle lands on side while getting out of difficult terrain, says MINDEF|website=Channel NewsAsia|date=16 September 2017|accessdate=5 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171127112044/http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/nsf-death-armoured-vehicle-lands-on-side-while-getting-out-of-9223014|archivedate=27 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-09-16/singapore-army-officer-dies-on-queensland-coast/8953582|title=Singapore Army officer dies in armoured vehicle crash on Queensland coast|website=ABC News (Australian Broadcasting Corporation)|date=16 September 2017|accessdate=5 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180214164501/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-09-16/singapore-army-officer-dies-o