ite-to-introduce-new-apprenticeship-based-technical-diploma-8766144 |title=ITE to introduce new apprenticeship-based technical diploma |website=Channel NewsAsia |access-date=28 November 2019 |date=7 March 2017}}</ref>\n**The [[Ministry of National Development (Singapore)|Ministry of National Development]] announced that [[JTC Corporation]] will be appointed the master developer of Punggol North, Singapore's first \"enterprise district\" housing digital and cybersecurity industries and connected to the future [[Singapore Institute of Technology]] campus. JTC will be allowed to vary land use instead of using zoning rules. A master developer will be appointed when Kampong Bugis, a residential district, is developed.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ng |first1=Jun Sen |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/housing/punggol-north-to-become-spores-first-enterprise-district-home-to-digital-and-cyber |title=Parliament: Punggol North to become Singapore's first 'enterprise district', home to digital and cyber-security industries |website=The Straits Times |access-date=6 November 2019 |date=7 March 2017}}</ref>\n* 9 March \u2013 The [[Ministry of Health (Singapore)|Ministry of Health]] announced a new 5-year Community Mental Health masterplan to improve [[mental health]] care, with help from agencies as well as services in polyclinics. Pallative care will also be strengthened too.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chia |first1=Lianne |title=5-year Community Mental Health master plan to be launched |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/5-year-community-mental-health-master-plan-to-be-launched-8773262 |website=CNA |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20171011024727/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/5-year-community-mental-health-master-plan-to-be-launched-8773262 |archivedate=11 October 2017 |accessdate=8 July 2019 |date=9 March 2017}}</ref>\n* 13 March - The [[Info-communications Media Development Authority]] awards FM89.3 and FM96.3 to [[Singapore Press Holdings]] (