 year concluded; the sentences of the six accused church pastors of [[City Harvest Church]] were shortened.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/city-harvest-appeal-kong-hee-s-sentence-reduced-to-3-5-years-8717606|title=City Harvest appeal: Kong Hee's sentence reduced to 3.5 years|website=Channel NewsAsia|access-date=2018-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705233039/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/city-harvest-appeal-kong-hee-s-sentence-reduced-to-3-5-years-8717606|archive-date=2018-07-05|url-status=live}}</ref> All the convicted pastors (with the exception of Chew Eng Han who was on bail; Chew later served his sentence on 22 February 2018) began their jail sentences on 21 April.\n* 9 April \u2013 [[United Overseas Bank]] and [[OCBC Bank]] announced that fees for their shared ATMs will be waived until the  to raise awareness of the scheme, in place since 1988.<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Boon|first1=Rachael|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/banking/free-cross-bank-atm-withdrawals-at-ocbc-uob|title=Free cross-bank ATM withdrawals at OCBC, UOB|date=10 April 2017|website=The Straits Times|access-date=10 August 2019}}</ref>\n* 10 April \u2013 The [[Ministry of Culture, Community and Youth]] announced that [[Esplanade \u2013 Theatres on the Bay|The Esplanade]] will be building a new mid-size waterfront theatre. Costing $30 million, the venue can seat 550 people and will be completed by 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/arts/new-30-million-waterfront-theatre-for-esplanade|title=New $30 million waterfront theatre for Esplanade|date=2017-04-10|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2019-06-18}}</ref>\n* 16 April \u2013 The [[Ministry of National Development (Singapore)|Ministry of National Development]] unveils Remaking our Heartland plans for Woodlands, with the vision \"Star of the North\". It will have new residential blocks in the north, as well as six new attractions i