cancer]] patients. The building will be ready by 2022.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Neo |first1=Chai Chin |title=New national cancer centre to be one-stop centre for cancer patients |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/new-national-cancer-centre-be-one-stop-centre-cancer-patients |website=Today |accessdate=7 July 2019 |date=2 June 2017}}</ref>\n* 7 June \u2013 [[Punggol Coast MRT station]] is announced to serve the future Punggol Creative Cluster, which has been brought forward from 2030 to 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Abdullah |first1=Zhaki |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/north-east-line-extension-to-open-in-2023-instead-of-2030-to-cater-to |title=North-East Line extension serving Punggol North to open in 2023 instead of 2030 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=28 April 2019 |date=7 June 2017}}</ref>\n* 11 June - The Braddell Flyover opens to traffic after three delays.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tan |first1=Christopher |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/long-delayed-braddell-flyover-to-open-on-june-11 |title=New Braddell Flyover to open on June 11 after repeated delays |website=The Straits Times |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=22 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Lai |first1=Linette |last2=Tan |first2=Audrey |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/braddell-flyover-finally-open-after-more-than-4-years-and-3-busted-deadlines |title=Braddell Flyover finally open after more than 4 years and 3 busted deadlines |website=The Straits Times |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=11 June 2017}}</ref>\n* 12 June \u2013 \n**An infant-care assistant became the first Singaporean woman to be detained under the [[Internal Security Act (Singapore)|Internal Security Act]] for radicalism.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/first-woman-held-under-isa-for-pro-isis-activities|title=First woman held under ISA for pro-ISIS activities|last=Cheong|first=Danson|date=13 June 2017|work=The Straits Times|access-date